commitResults.messageTitle: Updated FindCommand logic, now fully functional
commitResults.messageBody:
Upon executing FindCommand, it will create a new TaskList meant for
keeping track of matching tasks. Based on the input description given,
it will iterate through the tasklist and finds which task contains the
inputted description and appends them to the list

Finally, it outputs the matching tasks found based on the matching task
list size.
If 0: Custom message about no task found
Else: Custom message about task found

Also updated Task.java, added a getter for description

Also updated the toString() for TaskList.java, making it only display
the task now without the intro. This allows me to use it in both
FindCommand and ListCommand and just add the intro/outro accordingly to
what i need

commitResults.messageTitle: Add CI and fix Test files

commitResults.messageBody:
Added parser logic for update command. update takes in a mandatory field
index, while there are also multiple optional field,
/t <tasktype> used to declare a change in task type
/d <description> used to declare a new description
/by <DateTimeLocal> used to declare a new by. (This field is required if
a user is looking to change the current task types to be a Deadline
task)
/from <DateTimeLocal> used to declare a new from. (This field is
required if a user is looking to change the current Task to an Event
task)
/to <DateTimeLocal> used to declare a new to. (This field is required if
a user is looking to change the current Task to an Event Task)
*Do note, users are required to use at least one optional field when
using update)

Added UpdateCommand, like the other command types, it handles the logic
of excecuting the task. UpdateCommand uses the given inputs above and
creates a new updatedTask, after which it replaces the selectedTask with
it, thus updating the task.

Created getter for getBy for DeadlineTask
Created getters getFrom, getTo for EventTask
Created setIndex method in TaskList which takes a task and the index to
replace it at.

Added format for update command. Updated all other related thrown
exceptions to display the correct exception thrown.
